trans-unit.source: Serves as the base class for controls that reside in <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase"></xref> zones, and that provide catalogs of available Web server controls (especially <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart"></xref> controls) that users can add to a Web page.
trans-unit.target: Fungerer som basisklassen for kontroller som befinner seg i <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase"> </xref> soner, og som gir kataloger over tilgjengelige Web serverkontroller (spesielt <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart"> </xref> kontroller) som brukere kan legge til en webside.

trans-unit.source: The CatalogPart class is a base class for special controls that reside in <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase> zones.
trans-unit.target: CatalogPart klassen er en basisklasse for spesielle kontroller som befinner seg i <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase>soner.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase>

trans-unit.source: These derived CatalogPart controls provide catalogs of Web server controls that end users can add to a Web page.
trans-unit.target: Disse avledede CatalogPart kontroller gir kataloger for webserverkontroller sluttbrukere kan legge til en webside.

trans-unit.source: Use CatalogPart controls in a Web application when you want to provide end users with the flexibility to change the functionality of a Web page by adding or removing server controls.
trans-unit.target: Bruke CatalogPart kontroller i et webprogram hvis du vil gi sluttbrukere fleksibilitet til å endre funksjonaliteten til en webside ved å legge til eller fjerne serverkontroller.

trans-unit.source: A catalog is simply a list of one or more available Web server controls (including <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> controls, ASP.NET server controls, and custom or user controls) that users can add to a Web page.
trans-unit.target: En katalog er bare en liste over én eller flere tilgjengelige server webkontroller (inkludert <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>kontroller, ASP.NET serverkontroller og egendefinerte eller bruker kontroller) som brukere kan legge til en webside.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: A catalog has a number of common characteristics, including instruction text for end users; text to describe each server control; helper controls to select the server controls and add them to the page; a common header, footer, and border; and a number of style attributes.
trans-unit.target: En katalog har flere egenskaper, inkludert instruksjonene for sluttbrukere; tekst for å beskrive hver serverkontroll; Helper kontroller for å velge serverkontroller, og Legg dem til siden. en vanlig topptekst, bunntekst og kantlinje; og et antall Stilattributter.

trans-unit.source: There are three types of CatalogPart controls provided with the Web Parts control set, as described in the following table.
trans-unit.target: Det finnes tre kontrolltypene CatalogPart gav webdeler kontrollsett, som beskrevet i følgende tabell.

trans-unit.source: Each type of CatalogPart control contains server controls that are added to a page from a different source.
trans-unit.target: Hver kontrolltypen CatalogPart inneholder serverkontroller er lagt til en side fra en annen datakilde.

trans-unit.source: > [!IMPORTANT] > Controls that inherit from the CatalogPart class can reside only in zones derived from the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase> class.
trans-unit.target: > [!IMPORTANT] > Kontroller som arver fra klassen CatalogPart kan ligge i soner som er avledet fra <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase>klassen.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase>

trans-unit.source: |Control|Description| |-------------|-----------------| |<xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PageCatalogPart>|Contains controls that have been closed on a page, and that can be reopened (added back to the page) by users.
trans-unit.target: | Kontrollen | Beskrivelse | |-------------|-----------------| | <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PageCatalogPart>| Inneholder kontroller som har blitt lukket på en side, og som kan åpnes på nytt (tillagt tilbake til siden) av brukere.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PageCatalogPart>

trans-unit.source: The controls in this type of catalog are controls that were already added to the page from another source, and were then closed by a user.| |<xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.DeclarativeCatalogPart>|Contains server controls declared within a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.DeclarativeCatalogPart> control, which is itself contained in a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase> zone in the markup of a Web page.| |<xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.ImportCatalogPart>|Provides the user interface (UI) for a user to upload a control's definition file (an XML file defined by a schema, that contains state information) to a catalog, so that the control can be added to a Web page.
trans-unit.target: Kontroller i en katalog er kontrollene som er lagt til i siden fra en annen kilde, og deretter ble lukket av en bruker. | | <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.DeclarativeCatalogPart>| Inneholder serverkontroller som er angitt i en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.DeclarativeCatalogPart>kontroll, som også er i en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase>sone i koden for en webside. | | <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.ImportCatalogPart>| Gir brukergrensesnittet (UI) for en bruker til å laste opp en kontroll definisjonsfilen (definert av et skjema som inneholder informasjon om en XML-fil) i en katalog, slik at kontrollen kan legges til en webside.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.ImportCatalogPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.DeclarativeCatalogPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.DeclarativeCatalogPart>

trans-unit.source: The controls themselves do not appear in this type of catalog; the catalog is just a mechanism for accessing the definition files for external controls so they can be added to a page.| The CatalogPart class inherits from the base <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.Part> class, so that it has the common behavior of other part controls in the Web Parts control set.
trans-unit.target: Kontroller seg vises ikke i en mappe; katalogen er en metode for å få tilgang til definisjonsfilene for ekstern kontroller slik at de kan legges til en side. | CatalogPart klassen arver fra grunntallet <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.Part>class, slik at den har vanlige virkemåten for andre Delkontroller i webdeler kontrollen settet.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.Part>

trans-unit.source: In addition, it adds some members that are useful for the catalog functionality.
trans-unit.target: I tillegg noen medlemmer som er nyttige for katalog-funksjonalitet.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart.DisplayTitle%2A> property gets the actual string that is currently being displayed as the title of the control.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart.DisplayTitle%2A>egenskapen henter den faktiske strengen som vises som tittelen på kontrollen.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart.DisplayTitle%2A>

trans-unit.source: The value of this property can be the same as the value of the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.Part.Title%2A> property or, if no value has been assigned to that property, a default value supplied by the .NET Framework.
trans-unit.target: Verdien for denne egenskapen kan være den samme som verdien for den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.Part.Title%2A>egenskapen eller, hvis ingen verdi er tilordnet til denne egenskapen, en standardverdi ble levert av .NET Framework.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.Part.Title%2A>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart.WebPartManager%2A> and <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart.Zone%2A> properties both provide convenient access to the two essential objects that control the life cycle of a CatalogPart control: the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager> control, and the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase> zone that contains the CatalogPart control, respectively.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart.WebPartManager%2A>og <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart.Zone%2A>Egenskaper begge gir tilgang til de to viktige objektene som kontrollerer livssyklusen for en CatalogPart kontroll: den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager>kontrollen, og <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase>sone som inneholder CatalogPart-kontrollen henholdsvis.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart.Zone%2A> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart.WebPartManager%2A>

trans-unit.source: The CatalogPart class also contains several methods.
trans-unit.target: Klassen CatalogPart også inneholder flere metoder.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart.GetAvailableWebPartDescriptions%2A> method is declared as an abstract method that must be implemented by inheritors.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart.GetAvailableWebPartDescriptions%2A>metoden er deklarert som en abstrakt metode som må implementeres av inheritors.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart.GetAvailableWebPartDescriptions%2A>

trans-unit.source: Its intended purpose is to return a collection of descriptions of the controls in the catalog.
trans-unit.target: Formålet er å returnere en samling av beskrivelser av kontrollene i katalogen.

trans-unit.source: A related method, <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart.GetWebPart%2A>, is also declared as abstract and must be implemented by inheritors.
trans-unit.target: En relaterte metode <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart.GetWebPart%2A>også er deklarert som abstrakt og må implementeres av inheritors.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart.GetWebPart%2A>

trans-unit.source: This method is intended to return an instance of a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control based on a description that is passed to the method as a parameter.
trans-unit.target: Denne metoden er ikke ment å returnere en forekomst av en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>kontrollen basert på en beskrivelse som er sendt til metoden som en parameter.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: Initializes the class for use by an inherited class instance.
trans-unit.target: Initialiserer klasse for bruk av en arvet klasse-forekomst.

trans-unit.source: This constructor can only be called by an inherited class.
trans-unit.target: Denne konstruktøren, kan bare kalles med en arvet klasse.

trans-unit.source: Gets a string that contains the actual current title of a <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart"></xref> control.
trans-unit.target: Henter en streng som inneholder den faktiske gjeldende tittelen på en <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart"> </xref> kontrollen.

trans-unit.source: The DisplayTitle property returns either the current value of the base <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.Part.Title%2A> property or, if the control has no title, a calculated value.
trans-unit.target: Egenskapen DisplayTitle returnerer gjeldende verdi for grunntallet <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.Part.Title%2A>egenskapen eller, hvis kontrollen har ingen tittel, en beregnet verdi.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.Part.Title%2A>

trans-unit.source: The DisplayTitle property is designed to be a read-only, calculated property to get the actual current value of the displayed title at run time.
trans-unit.target: Egenskapen DisplayTitle er utformet for å være en skrivebeskyttet, beregnet til å hente den faktiske verdien for gjeldende for vises på kjøretidspunktet.

trans-unit.source: Therefore, you should not attempt to use this property to set a title for a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart> control.
trans-unit.target: Derfor bør du ikke prøve å bruke denne egenskapen til å angi en tittel for en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>kontroll.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>

trans-unit.source: To set a title, use the base <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.Part.Title%2A> property.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du vil angi en tittel, kan du bruke grunntallet <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.Part.Title%2A>egenskapen.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.Part.Title%2A>

trans-unit.source: A string that represents the complete, visible title of the control.
trans-unit.target: En streng som representerer fullført, vises tittelen på kontrollen.

trans-unit.source: The default value is an empty string ("").
trans-unit.target: Standardverdien er en tom streng ("").

trans-unit.source: Returns a collection of descriptions of the available <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart"></xref> controls in a catalog.
trans-unit.target: Returnerer en samling av beskrivelser av de tilgjengelige <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart"> </xref> kontroller i en katalog.

trans-unit.source: The GetAvailableWebPartDescriptions method returns description information for each control in a catalog.
trans-unit.target: Metoden GetAvailableWebPartDescriptions returnerer beskrivelsesinformasjon for hver kontroll i en katalog.

trans-unit.source: A <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartDescription> object is a lightweight object that contains essential information about a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control, including its ID, an object reference to the control, and the values of several important properties that are inherited from the base <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.Part> class, such as <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.Part.Title%2A> and <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.Part.Description%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Et <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartDescription>objekt er en lett objekt som inneholder viktig informasjon om en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>kontroll, inkludert IDen, en objektreferanse til kontrollen, og verdiene for flere viktige egenskaper som er arvet fra den første <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.Part>klasse, for eksempel <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.Part.Title%2A>og <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.Part.Description%2A>.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.Part.Description%2A> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.Part.Title%2A> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.Part> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartDescription>

trans-unit.source: The GetAvailableWebPartDescriptions method improves performance.
trans-unit.target: Metoden GetAvailableWebPartDescriptions øker ytelsen.

trans-unit.source: When a catalog is created, it needs some information about each control it contains, including a title, a description, an icon (if one exists), and an ID.
trans-unit.target: Når en katalog er opprettet, må den inn informasjon om hver kontroll den inneholder, inkludert en tittel, en beskrivelse, et ikon (Hvis det finnes) og en ID

trans-unit.source: Rather than having to create an instance of each control to get this information, a caller can use the GetAvailableWebPartDescriptions method, which returns only the description information about each control.
trans-unit.target: En oppringer kan bruke metoden GetAvailableWebPartDescriptions som returnerer bare beskrivelsesinformasjon om hver kontroll i stedet for å opprette en forekomst av hver kontroll få denne informasjonen.

trans-unit.source: A <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartDescriptionCollection"></xref> that contains a <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartDescription"></xref> for each control in a catalog.
trans-unit.target: En <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartDescriptionCollection"> </xref> som inneholder en <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartDescription"> </xref> for hver kontroll i en katalog.

trans-unit.source: Retrieves the current state of a <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart"></xref> control's parent zone.
trans-unit.target: Henter gjeldende status for en <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart"> </xref> kontrollens overordnede sone.

trans-unit.source: The GetDesignModeState method returns information about the state of the zone that contains a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart> control.
trans-unit.target: Metoden GetDesignModeState returnerer informasjon om tilstanden til sonen som inneholder en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>kontroll.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>

trans-unit.source: The state information is returned in the form of a dictionary.
trans-unit.target: Tilstandsinformasjonen returneres i form av en ordliste.

trans-unit.source: An <xref:System.Collections.IDictionary> that contains the current state of the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase"></xref> zone that contains a <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart"></xref> control.
trans-unit.target: En <xref:System.Collections.IDictionary>som inneholder den gjeldende tilstanden til den <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase"> </xref> sone som inneholder en <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart"> </xref> kontroll.</xref:System.Collections.IDictionary>

trans-unit.source: Retrieves from a catalog the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart"></xref> control that is referenced by the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartDescription"></xref> object passed to the method.
trans-unit.target: Henter fra en katalog i <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart"> </xref> kontrollen som refererer til den <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartDescription"> </xref> objekt sendt til metoden.

trans-unit.source: The GetWebPart method returns a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control from a catalog.
trans-unit.target: Metoden GetWebPart returnerer en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>kontrollen fra en katalog.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartDescription> object that is passed to the method matches a specific <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control and enables that control to be returned by the method.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartDescription>objekt som er sendt til metoden samsvarer med en bestemt <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>kontrollerer og aktiverer som styrer som skal returneres ved hjelp av metoden.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartDescription>

trans-unit.source: If a catalog contains a server control that does not derive from the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> class, such as an ASP.NET server control, a custom server control, or a user control, a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart> control must wrap the server control with a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart> control, and return the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart> control from this method.
trans-unit.target: Hvis en katalog inneholder en serverkontroll ikke avledes fra den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>klasse, for eksempel en ASP.NET-serverkontroll, en egendefinert serverkontroll eller en brukerkontroll en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>kontrollen må bryte serverkontroll med en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart>kontrollere, og returnerer det <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart>kontrollen fra denne metoden.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: A <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartDescription"></xref> that contains a reference to a specific <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart"></xref>.
trans-unit.target: En <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartDescription"> </xref> som inneholder en referanse til en bestemt <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart"> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: A that is referenced by the object in the description parameter.
trans-unit.target: En som refererer til objektet i den description parameteren.

trans-unit.source: Raises the <xref href="System.Web.UI.Control.PreRender"></xref> event.
trans-unit.target: Hever den <xref href="System.Web.UI.Control.PreRender"> </xref> hendelsen.

trans-unit.source: The OnPreRender method calls the base <xref:System.Web.UI.Control.OnPreRender%2A?displayProperty=fullName> method, and ensures that an instance of the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase> class has been created.
trans-unit.target: OnPreRender metodekall grunntallet <xref:System.Web.UI.Control.OnPreRender%2A?displayProperty=fullName>metode, og sikrer at en forekomst av den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase>klassen har blitt opprettet.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase> </xref:System.Web.UI.Control.OnPreRender%2A?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: An <xref:System.EventArgs> that contains the event data.
trans-unit.target: En <xref:System.EventArgs>som inneholder Hendelsesdata.</xref:System.EventArgs>

trans-unit.source: The <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase"></xref> that contains the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart"></xref> control is <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""></xref>.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase"> </xref> som inneholder den <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart"> </xref> kontrollen er <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: Sets design-time data for a control.
trans-unit.target: Angir utformingen data for en kontroll.

trans-unit.source: An <xref:System.Collections.IDictionary> containing the design-time data for the control.
trans-unit.target: En <xref:System.Collections.IDictionary>som inneholder utformingen dataene for kontrollen.</xref:System.Collections.IDictionary>

trans-unit.source: Gets a reference to the current instance of the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager"></xref> class.
trans-unit.target: Henter en referanse til den gjeldende forekomsten av den <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager"> </xref> klasse.

trans-unit.source: The WebPartManager property provides a way for a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart> control to access the current <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager> object on the page.
trans-unit.target: Egenskapen WebPartManager inneholder en metode for en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>kontrollen for å få tilgang til gjeldende <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager>objekt på siden.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>

trans-unit.source: The <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager"></xref> for the current Web page.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager"> </xref> for gjeldende websiden.

trans-unit.source: Gets a reference to the <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase"></xref> zone that contains a <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart"></xref> control.
trans-unit.target: Henter en referanse til det <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase"> </xref> sone som inneholder en <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart"> </xref> kontrollen.

trans-unit.source: The Zone property enables a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart> control to get a reference to its zone.
trans-unit.target: Sone egenskapen aktiverer en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>kontrollen for å hente en referanse til sonen.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPart>

trans-unit.source: Although the property is read-only, the underlying properties of the zone itself can be changed programmatically.
trans-unit.target: Selv om egenskapen er skrivebeskyttet, kan du endre underliggende egenskaper for sonen selve programmatisk.

trans-unit.source: A <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase"></xref> that corresponds to the zone that contains the control.
trans-unit.target: En <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogZoneBase"> </xref> som tilsvarer sonen som inneholder kontrollen.
